<br>
If the USA had 0 guns, would there be less murders? Possibly. There's no way you can say yes or no. Humans by nature can be violent, creative, and extremely resourceful.<br>
<br>
There is no utopian society free of death and violence. If anyone gets close, it won't stay that way for long. You can't choose to ignore human behavior and your inability to predict or control other people's actions, ideas, and desires. The potential to be evil is in each and every one of us and it will not be cleaned away by eliminating the current standard for weaponry.<br>
<br>
The history of humans and firearms is shorter than the history of humans without firearms. Before guns existed there was murder, war, and extreme violence. I would argue that the distant past is far more violent than the present.<br>
<br>
The thing to concentrate on is the USA's society. The problems and solutions with violence are in the culture, at least for the most part. Obviously wackos are born that would be rotten and evil regardless of environment. If murder is going to decline, it will do so because of changes to society and family.<br>
<br>
Here are some interesting numbers...<br>
<br>
USA homicides per 100k persons:<br>
<br>
9.8 in 1991 and falling to 5.5 by 2000<br>
<br>
1976-2000 USA homicides:<br>
<br>
-63.8% committed by ages 18-34<br>
<br>
Of those homicides the relationship between offender and victim is:<br>
<br>
-47.3% Intimate<br>
-49.5% Family<br>
<br>
Circumstance:<br>
<br>
(obviously some homicides are related to more than 1)<br>
<br>
-74.3% Sex related<br>
-75.9% Drug related<br>
-65.6% Gang related<br>
<br>
Weapon:<br>
<br>
(obviously some homicides are related to more than 1)<br>
<br>
-62.4% Gun<br>
-58.6% Arson<br>
-53.2% Poison<br>
<br>
Now. Would removing gangs from society have an impact on homicide? Definately. Would people capable of murder still commit homicide if taken out of a gang environment? Possibly. They have it in them, apparently.<br>
<br>
Would removing guns from society have an impact on murder? Possibly. As you can see, people are very willing to kill each other in other ways. Who's to say if you remove guns that arson, poison, and other means of committing murder won't simply rise to compensate? You can't.<br>
<br>
Guns happen to be the current weapon of choice. If you remove that, the weapon of choice will shift to something else. Read your history.<br>
<br>
If you blame guns for violence in USA, you're focusing on the wrong thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=merraharvaz>MerraharVaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 416<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/7/03 2:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=208.topic&index=52>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gang violence</span><hr size=1> I agree with that, Krol. To murder somebody, you have to pass a certain threshold. Once you reach that threshold, you will murder somebody any way you can.<br>
<br>
But, I think that the threshold for murdering somebody with a gun is significantly lower than with for instance a knife. You don't take the root of the violence away with guns, but I think without easy accessibility to guns, the number of gundeaths would go down significantly.<br>
<br>
Of course, it would do nothing against people who are determined to murder somebody. But the massive violence between gangs is just not possible without guns (think of drive-bys and assasinations like that). Also, I believe that less murders would occur by people who murder out of impulse and less of murders by relative (which by your number is a large portion of all murders.<br>
<br>
Guns are made to make killing more easy, there's a reason that in conflicts like Liberia they disarm the factions.<br>
<br>
That said, with or without guns, the root of the problem still remains. <p>---------------<br>
